<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.542/39</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">German Ambassador</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2226</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt, in due course, of your note of November 13, 1916, wherein
                            [etc.].</p>
                        <p>In reply I have the honor to say that a translation of your note has been
                            sent to the Secretary of the Interior, for the information and
                            consideration of the Commissioner of Patents, and that upon receipt of
                            his reply you will be advised thereof.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>